title: Ohio State-Rutgers turning into a hot ticket?
text:
FOXSPORTS Ohio State-Rutgers turning into a hot ticket? Fans who want to see the Buckeyes and Scarlet Knights in person will have to go somewhere other than the box office. 
Fans fill the stands during a game between the Rutgers Scarlet Knights and Penn State Nittany Lions at High Point Solutions Stadium. Alex Goodlett / Getty Images North America By Marcus Hartman Oct 22, 2015 at 11:05a ET 0Shares 
Ohio State football is headed to Piscataway, N.J., to play its first game at Rutgers , and apparently there is some excitement for the matchup. 
The Scarlet Knights athletics department announced Wednesday the game at High Point Solutions Stadium is sold out. 
This marks the fourth sellout in six Big Ten home games since Rutgers joined the league last year. 
It will be the seventh sellout since a stadium expansion project was completed in 2009. 
Rutgers set a stadium record with 53,774 fans for Penn State's visit last season. 
Meanwhile, Ohio State figures to be in for a change of pace from last week when it played in front of a home crowd of 108,423 fans while beating Penn State 38-10. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters. 0
